
              *DHCP Spoofing*
              
- Open Ettercap.
- Select DHCP Spoofing.
- Specify the IP pool range (e.g., 10.10.10.110-120).
- Enter the netmask.
- Set the DNS server IP to the attacker's IP.
- Open Wireshark to monitor.

DHCP Starvation:
- Continuously send discover packets.
- This will keep the DHCP server busy.
- It is a kind of DoS attack on the DHCP server.
- Yersinia tool can be used for this.